Class PIDControl

Direct Known Subclasses:
Main.PosPID, Main.VelPID, RealMotorSamples.PosPID, ScorbotJogHome.PosPID, ScorbotSamples.PosPID
public abstract class PIDControl
extends SISOFeedback

PID controller for single-input, single-output systems. This class is used as an extension of the SISOFeedback class and implements the PID algorithm. This class is also abstract -- to use it the user must 'extend' this class and define FindProcessValue() and PutActuationValue(double val) so the controller can get its input and know where to place its output.

Author:
DMAuslander July 14, 2009

Parameters:

sys - The TrjSys in which this task is embedded
dt - Controller sampler interval
mMin - Minimum actuation value that is allowed
mMax - Maximum ...
mOff - Actuation value to use when controller is 'Off'
initialState - State that is entered when task is first activated
taskActive - 'true' if task is active
kp - Controller gains
ki - ...
kd - ...
integ0 - Initial value of integrator
triggerMode - 'true' if controller only runs directly after some other task task runs (usually that is a Supervisory task)
